<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="278" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,591,890,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Material examined. PROTEKER 3:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[602,705,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Ile Suhm</emphasis>
, a tuft of stems up to 
<quantity box="[977,1060,890,917]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
high, with gonophores (
<collectionCode box="[1349,1436,891,917]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">MNHN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[151,181,927,953]" country="Ukraine" name="Zoological Institute, Ukrainian Academy of Sciences" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">IK</collectionCode>
–2012–10428).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="278" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,962,988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Description.</emphasis>
Stems up to 
<quantity box="[491,571,962,989]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
high, unbranched or with only a few secondary stems (one stem gives rise to seven secondary stems and some of these to one, on one occasion two, third-order stems). Degree of stem annulation variable, but in general stems strong and densely ringed, smooth distally. No distal perisarc collar. Polyps with around 36 tentacles; five in a whorl around hypostome (
<figureCitation box="[778,867,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,183,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1436,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Coryne pusilla Gaertner, 1774: A, distal part of polyp; B, larger and smaller stenoteles. Eudendrium tottoni Stechow, 1932: C, polyp; D, hydranth’s basal annular swelling; E, male gonophore. Tubularia sp.: F, hydranth and gonophores. Scale bar: 900 µm (F), 600 µm (F close-up), 200 µm (A), 100 µm (C, E), 50 µm (D), 10 µm (B)." pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), the remaining with no clear arrangement.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">One or two little-developed gonophores present in a few polyps, originating at axil of basal tentacles. Gonophores roughly spherical, attached by a small pedicel to hydranth body. One 340 µm high and 270 µm in maximum diameter; another 240 µm in diameter.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
Cnidome consisting of stenoteles in two size classes (
<figureCitation box="[807,897,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1658,1682]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,183,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-27@5.[151,1436,181,1634]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Coryne pusilla Gaertner, 1774: A, distal part of polyp; B, larger and smaller stenoteles. Eudendrium tottoni Stechow, 1932: C, polyp; D, hydranth’s basal annular swelling; E, male gonophore. Tubularia sp.: F, hydranth and gonophores. Scale bar: 900 µm (F), 600 µm (F close-up), 200 µm (A), 100 µm (C, E), 50 µm (D), 10 µm (B)." pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
): larger 20.1±1.1 x 12.9±0.7 µm (n= 10), range 18–22 x 12.0–14.0 µm, smaller 12.3±0.5 x 7.5±0.4 µm (n= 10), range 11.5–13.0 x 6.5–8.0 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="278" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1287,1313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Allman, G. J." box="[325,493,1287,1313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="113 - 115" refId="ref7018" refString="Allman, G. J. (1876) Descriptions of some new species of Hydroida from Kerguelen's Island. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 4, 17, 113 - 115. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937608681913" type="journal article" year="1876">Allman (1876)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Peña Cantero, 2022" authorityName="Peña Cantero" authorityYear="2022" box="[619,804,1287,1313]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[619,804,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[814,877,1287,1313]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Kerguelen. His brief description, based on infertile material, precludes assigning any material to this species. The present material could be conspecific with Allman’s, agreeing in general with the few characters he described, but the species is not sufficiently characterised. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[151,346,1395,1421]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="739 - 878" refId="ref8321" refString="Schuchert, P. (2001) Survey of the family Corynidae (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 108 (4), 739 - 878. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80165" type="journal article" year="2001">Schuchert (2001)</bibRefCitation>
already considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peña Cantero" authorityYear="2022" box="[574,701,1395,1421]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis box="[574,701,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">C. conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
an insufficiently described species, being indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" box="[151,260,1431,1457]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[151,260,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="Allman, 1859" authorityName="Allman" authorityYear="1859" box="[297,624,1430,1457]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="eximia">
<emphasis box="[297,462,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne eximia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Allman, G. J." box="[467,624,1430,1457]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="137 - 144" refId="ref6977" refString="Allman, G. J. (1859) Notes on the hydroid zoophytes. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 3, 4, 137 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935908697098" type="journal article" year="1859">Allman, 1859</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peña Cantero" authorityYear="2022" box="[199,384,1467,1493]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis box="[199,384,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was again reported from Kerguelen, also based on infertile material, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Studer, T." box="[1229,1386,1467,1493]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="104 - 141" refId="ref8439" refString="Studer, T. (1879) Die Fauna von Kerguelensland. Verzeichniss der bis jetzt auf Kerguelensland beobachteten Thierspecies nebst kurzen Notizen uber ihr Vorkommen und ihre zoogeographischen Beziehungen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 45, 104 - 141." type="journal article" year="1879">Studer (1879)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[151,352,1503,1529]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="269 - 340" refId="ref8525" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1910) Die Hydroiden der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903, 11 (Zoology 3), 269 - 340." type="journal article" year="1910">Vanhöffen (1910)</bibRefCitation>
; the latter from the same locality as Allman’s material.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
I have assigned the present material to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" box="[629,793,1539,1565]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[629,793,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it agrees with this species in the colony habit, the lack of perisarc collar at the end of the stem, the number of tentacles on the polyp and the size of the nematocysts. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[307,501,1611,1637]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="739 - 878" refId="ref8321" refString="Schuchert, P. (2001) Survey of the family Corynidae (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 108 (4), 739 - 878. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80165" type="journal article" year="2001">Schuchert (2001)</bibRefCitation>
the stems are 
<quantity box="[664,748,1611,1637]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" unit="cm" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3 cm</quantity>
high, with five to 15 hydranths per shoot and rarely end in a funnel-shaped dilation; the polyps are provided with 18–28 tentacles. As for the size of the nematocysts, he reported stenoteles 18–23 x 11–15 µm and 12–16 x 6.5–10 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,890,1997]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[199,396,1719,1745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="739 - 878" refId="ref8321" refString="Schuchert, P. (2001) Survey of the family Corynidae (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 108 (4), 739 - 878. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80165" type="journal article" year="2001">Schuchert (2001)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" box="[571,740,1719,1745]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[571,740,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known from Kerguelen, but without providing a direct reference. He probably refers to 
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[525,803,1754,1781]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="269 - 340" refId="ref8525" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1910) Die Hydroiden der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903, 11 (Zoology 3), 269 - 340." type="journal article" year="1910">Vanhöffen’s (1910: 275)</bibRefCitation>
record, which was described just after his record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peña Cantero" authorityYear="2022" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">C. conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Kerguelen. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert, P." box="[444,695,1791,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="739 - 878" refId="ref8321" refString="Schuchert, P. (2001) Survey of the family Corynidae (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 108 (4), 739 - 878. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 80165" type="journal article" year="2001">Schuchert (2001: 849)</bibRefCitation>
stated that “ 
<bibRefCitation author="Vanhoffen, E." box="[834,1035,1791,1817]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" pagination="269 - 340" refId="ref8525" refString="Vanhoffen, E. (1910) Die Hydroiden der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903, 11 (Zoology 3), 269 - 340." type="journal article" year="1910">Vanhöffen (1910)</bibRefCitation>
described infertile 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peña Cantero" authorityYear="2022" box="[1253,1436,1791,1817]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="conferta">
<emphasis box="[1253,1436,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne conferta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
colonies from close to the 
<typeStatus box="[451,499,1827,1853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">type</typeStatus>
locality and also fertile colonies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" box="[907,1073,1827,1853]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[907,1073,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Coryne pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on floating 
<emphasis box="[1212,1295,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[1212,1286,1827,1853]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Fucaceae" genus="Fucus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">Fucus</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
. Even when Vanhöffen’s material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" box="[419,526,1863,1889]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[419,526,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[722,790,1863,1888]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Fucaceae" genus="Fucus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Fucales" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[722,790,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">Fucus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as Schuchert indicated, it does not come from Kerguelen, but from the English Channel. Therefore, if confirmed, the present material would represent the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaertner" authorityYear="1774" class="Hydrozoa" family="Corynidae" genus="Coryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anthoathecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="278" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="278">C. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the study area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
